# Cloudflare MCP and Cursor persistence

## Token reality (verified in SSOT tooling)

**Vault:** **1Password** is the **only** program secrets vault; Cursor retrieves via **Environments `envFile`**, **`op read`** wrappers, or **1Password service accounts** — see **`CURSOR_1PASSWORD_DEVELOPER_VAULT_2026-04-27.md`** **Vault policy**.

Most Cloudflare MCP servers in Cursor pass the account API credential via **stdin / process env** (see **`CURSOR_CLOUDFLARE_MCP_AND_PLUGIN_SSOT.md`** for the canonical env key name). **`user-cloudflare-docs`** and **`user-cloudflare-agents-sdk`** search tools operate without account API scopes; API-bound servers share the **same** full-function account token: **`developer`** vault item title **`CF-MCP-FULL-OBS-BINDINGS-API`** must **match** the Cloudflare dashboard token **name** exactly ([`CURSOR_1PASSWORD_DEVELOPER_VAULT_2026-04-27.md`](https://github.com/centexmsp/repository-restructuring/blob/main/docs/CURSOR_1PASSWORD_DEVELOPER_VAULT_2026-04-27.md)). [`mcp-server-auth-wrapper.sh`](https://github.com/centexmsp/repository-restructuring/blob/main/scripts/mcp-server-auth-wrapper.sh) tries **Keychain/libsecret before any `op` session bootstrap** — **Touch ID path runs only when the token is absent from disk** and **`op read`** becomes necessary (**`OP_SERVICE_ACCOUNT_TOKEN`** still implies fully unattended **`op`**). Prefer **`export OP_INTERACTIVE_OP_UNLOCK=0`** with service account **or** pre-synced OS store **or** warm **`op whoami`**. Do **not** invent separate MCP tokens unless a server documentation explicitly differs.

On **Mac/Linux**, prefer **1Password Environments** → FIFO **`.cursor/cloudflare-mcp.env`** + Cursor MCP **`envFile`** (**[`docs/CURSOR_CLOUDFLARE_MCP_AND_PLUGIN_SSOT.md`](https://github.com/centexmsp/repository-restructuring/blob/main/docs/CURSOR_CLOUDFLARE_MCP_AND_PLUGIN_SSOT.md)** **§3.10**); [`lib-cloudflare-credentials.sh`](https://github.com/centexmsp/repository-restructuring/blob/main/scripts/lib-cloudflare-credentials.sh) sources the same paths for deploy when vars are unset. Otherwise **[`scripts/mcp-server-auth-wrapper.sh`](https://github.com/centexmsp/repository-restructuring/blob/main/scripts/mcp-server-auth-wrapper.sh)** (**Keychain** / **`op read`**) or **`${env:…}`** in **`mcp.json`**. The **1Password Cursor plugin** validates mounts; **`1Password.op-vscode`** does not replace **`envFile`** for MCP children. **Cursor Agent “Run command”** may fail while MCP still works — **`CURSOR_CLOUDFLARE_MCP_AND_PLUGIN_SSOT.md`** **§3.12**. **`op whoami`** can fail after **delegated session** timeout while **Terminal.app** still works — run **`./scripts/diagnose-centex-cloudflare-env.sh`**; **`CURSOR_1PASSWORD_DEVELOPER_VAULT_2026-04-27.md`** **Delegated CLI sessions**.

## After Cursor updates or MCP auth drift

Operators should **`export OP_SERVICE_ACCOUNT_TOKEN=…`** (or sync Keychain) then **`./scripts/verify-cloudflare-integration.sh`**; optional **`./scripts/op-ensure-session.sh`** only for interactive **`op`** recovery. Cursor may prompt to **re-approve** MCP configs or toggle servers under **Features → Model Context Protocol** — that is independent of `.cursor/rules` reloading.

See also: [`CONTINUE_ENGINEERING_PLAYBOOK_SSOT.md`](https://github.com/centexmsp/repository-restructuring/blob/main/docs/CONTINUE_ENGINEERING_PLAYBOOK_SSOT.md) §§8–9 · [`CURSOR_1PASSWORD_DEVELOPER_VAULT_2026-04-27.md`](https://github.com/centexmsp/repository-restructuring/blob/main/docs/CURSOR_1PASSWORD_DEVELOPER_VAULT_2026-04-27.md).
